Body mass of penguins throughout the years, species of penguins across islands, sex ratio within species, bill length vs bill depth ##Visualising the data #Body mass of diff species of Penguins throughout the years ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} MessyPenguins_modified3 %>% gf_bar(year ~ body_mass) %>% gf_labs(x = "Body Mass", y = "Year", title = "Body mass of different species of Penguins throughout the years") ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` Warning: Ignoring unknown aesthetics: . ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr} ``` Warning: The following aesthetics were dropped during statistical transformation: .. ℹ This can happen when ggplot fails to infer the correct grouping structure in the data. ℹ Did you forget to specify a `group` aesthetic or to convert a numerical variable into a factor? ``` ::: ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](exploration-16th_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: #Body mass of diff species and sex of Penguins throughout the years ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} MessyPenguins_modified3 %>% gf_line(year ~ body_mass, color =~ sex) %>% gf_labs(x = "Body Mass", y = "Year", title = "Body mass of different species of Penguins throughout the years") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](exploration-16th_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=672} ::: ::: #Species of Penguins across islands ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} MessyPenguins_modified3 %>% gf_point(island ~ species) %>% gf_labs(x = "Species", y = "Island", title = "Species of Penguins across Islands") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} ![](exploration-16th_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-9-1.png){width=672} ::: :::
